PubPeer是一个允许用户在发表后讨论和审查科学研究的网站，即发表后的同行评审，名稱是結合public（大眾）和Peer review（[[同行評審|同行評審]]），屬於{{link-ja|出版後查證|出版後査読}}的網站，使用者以研究所學生及年輕的研究員為主<ref>{{cite web|url=http://udn.com/news/story/10586/2114453|title=閱報秘書╱PubPeer 審論平台|publisher=聯合新聞網|author=鄭語謙|date=2016-11-18|accessdate=2016-11-20|archive-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119154803/http://udn.com/news/story/10586/2114453|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但因為允許匿名評論，也被質疑其公信力有問題<ref name=chinatimes>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinatimes.com/newspapers/20161120000270-260114|title=PubPeer匿名舉報 公信力備受爭議|publisher=中時電子報|author=余祥|date=2016-11-20|accessdate=2016-11-20|archive-date=2016-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161120145333/http://www.chinatimes.com/newspapers/20161120000270-260114|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upmedia.mg/news_info.php?SerialNo=8215|title=獨家》被爆料論文造假　中研院學者反控PubPeer公信力不足|author=張若瑤|publisher=上報|date=2016-11-29|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2016-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202173826/http://www.upmedia.mg/news_info.php?SerialNo=8215|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

该网站已经成为一个举报平台，因为它强调了几篇引人注目的论文的缺点，曾导致了撤回和科学欺诈指控，如Retraction Watch一样所被人闻名。 与大多数平台相反，它允许对发表后的文章进行匿名评论，这是一个有争议的特点，亦是其成功的主要因素。因此，不少作者指控PubPeer的一些用户存在诽谤的行为。

==歷史==
PubPeer在2012年10月成立，2015年10月起改為匿名運作，運作者分別是[[法國國家科學研究中心|法國國家科學研究中心]]的神經科學家Brandon Stell<ref>{{cite news|title=Pioneer behind controversial PubPeer site reveals his identity|url=http://www.nature.com/news/pioneer-behind-controversial-pubpeer-site-reveals-his-identity-1.18261|newspaper=Nature|date=2015-08-31|accessdate=2016-11-17|archive-date=2015-09-01|archive-url=https://archive.is/20150901010312/http://www.nature.com/news/pioneer-behind-controversial-pubpeer-site-reveals-his-identity-1.18261|dead-url=no}}</ref>，另外二人的[[用户|用户名]]分別是George Smith及Richard Smith<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nature.com/news/pioneer-behind-controversial-pubpeer-site-reveals-his-identity-1.18261 |author=Ewen Callaway |title=Pioneer behind controversial PubPeer site reveals his identity |publisher=Nature |date=2015-08-31 |accessdate=2016-02-24 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150901010312/http://www.nature.com/news/pioneer-behind-controversial-pubpeer-site-reveals-his-identity-1.18261 |archivedate=2015-09-01 }}</ref>。

==簡介==

有些網站和PubPeer的性質類似，都是讓學術研究者可以進行出版後的[[同行評審|同行評審]]。PubPeer強調一些高调论文的缺點，指控研究者進行[[科學不端行為|科研造假]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Researcher admits mistakes in stem cell study|url=http://www.timeslive.co.za/lifestyle/2013/05/27/researcher-admits-mistakes-in-stem-cell-study|newspaper=Times live|date=2013-05-27|accessdate=2016-11-17|archive-date=2016-05-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160527051240/http://www.timeslive.co.za/lifestyle/2013/05/27/researcher-admits-mistakes-in-stem-cell-study|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Zellbiologe gibt Fehler in Klonstudie zu|url=http://www.zeit.de/wissen/gesundheit/2013-05/klonen-studie-fehler-mitalipov-reaktion|newspaper=Zeit|date=2013-05|accessdate=2016-11-17|archive-date=2016-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114005034/http://www.zeit.de/wissen/gesundheit/2013-05/klonen-studie-fehler-mitalipov-reaktion|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Stem-cell cloner acknowledges errors in groundbreaking paper|url=http://www.nature.com/news/stem-cell-cloner-acknowledges-errors-in-groundbreaking-paper-1.13060|newspaper=Nature|accessdate=2016-11-17|archive-date=2016-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161216130002/http://www.nature.com/news/stem-cell-cloner-acknowledges-errors-in-groundbreaking-paper-1.13060|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='STAPgate' shows Japan must get back to basics in science|url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2014/04/20/national/stapgate-shows-japan-must-get-back-to-basics-in-science/#.U2skY8fTZss|newspaper=apanTimes|date=2014-04-20|accessdate=2016-11-17|archive-date=2017-08-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831002017/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2014/04/20/national/stapgate-shows-japan-must-get-back-to-basics-in-science/#.U2skY8fTZss|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=台大論文接連惹議 楊泮池痛心致歉|url=http://www.cna.com.tw/news/firstnews/201611150350-1.aspx|newspaper=中央通訊社|date=2016-11-15|accessdate=2016-11-17|archive-date=2016-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117211911/http://www.cna.com.tw/news/firstnews/201611150350-1.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>，甚至會讓發表[[論文|論文]]被{{le|撤銷|retractions}}。在{{le|Retraction Watch|Retraction Watch}} blog中也曾提到PubPeer的特點<ref>{{cite web |url=http://retractionwatch.com/2015/01/12/leading-diabetes-researcher-corrects-paper-dozen-studies-questioned-pubpeer/ |title=Leading diabetes researcher corrects paper as more than a dozen studies are questioned on PubPeer - Retraction Watch at Retraction Watch |publisher=Retractionwatch.com |date=2016-04-26 |accessdate=2016-11-17 |archive-date=2016-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161029095649/http://retractionwatch.com/2015/01/12/leading-diabetes-researcher-corrects-paper-dozen-studies-questioned-pubpeer/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

PubPeer中討論的问题多半是論文中{{le|捏造 (科学)|Fabrication (science)|捏造}}或是{{link-ja|變造|改ざん (科学)}}[[資料|資料]]，或是有[[抄襲|抄襲]]他人論文的情形。像日本學者[[小保方晴子|小保方晴子]]在2014年春天於《[[自然_(期刊)|自然]]》期刊上發表了世界首例有效製作[[STAP細胞|STAP細胞]]的論文，在2014年1月29日論文發表後就在PubPeer有許多的議論，幾天後就被人指出有數據異常的问题<ref name="pub_Obo">{{Cite web |url=https://pubpeer.com/publications/8B755710BADFE6FB0A848A44B70F7D |title=PubPeer - Stimulus-triggered fate conversion of somatic cells into pluripotency |accessdate=2016-02-24 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140903095612/https://pubpeer.com/publications/8B755710BADFE6FB0A848A44B70F7D |archivedate=2014-09-03 }}</ref>。

申請PubPeer的帳號，需要有[[PubMed|PubMed]]期刊資料庫的帳號才能在PubPeer上进行註冊（即PubMed資料庫收錄期刊的第一作者或是通訊作者才能申請帳號<ref name=chinatimes/>），但平台上的發言采用匿名方式進行。

部分PubPeer用戶曾被指控[[诽谤|诽谤]]，有些已和解<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/news/can-post-publication-peer-review-endure/2016895.article | journal=THE | title=Can post-publication peer review endure? | date=2014-12-13 | accessdate=2014-12-05 | author=Paul Jump | archive-date=2014-11-17 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141117001603/http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/news/can-post-publication-peer-review-endure/2016895.article | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://pubpeer.com/topics/1/3F5792FF283A624FB48E773CAAD150 | title=PubPeer's first legal threat | author=Peer 0 | date=2014-08-24 | accessdate=2014-12-05 | format=blog | archive-date=2014-12-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141208122908/https://pubpeer.com/topics/1/3F5792FF283A624FB48E773CAAD150 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，PubPeer的評論只能可公開驗證的事實<ref>{{cite web |url=https://pubpeer.com/howto |title=pubpeer howto |publisher=Pubpeer.com |date=2006-05-17 |accessdate=2016-11-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115164005/https://pubpeer.com/howto |archivedate=2016-11-15 }}</ref>。

